[OWNS]
- [1] Staged command execution, command input, document mutation receipts, selection, options, prompt flow, and command-visible transactions
- [2] Capture-specific policies, outputs, raster/PDF bridge points, and visual evidence surfaces when separated from camera state
- [3] Rhino geometry construction and projection: primitives, curves, surfaces, Breps, extrusions, meshes, SubD, transforms, framed bounds, annotations, and block/document/preview-ready output
- [4] File capabilities, archive/publish/import/export, sheet edits, linked resources, raster/PDF policy, and typed receipts
- [5] Viewport target resolution, live camera state, camera mutation, projections, frustums, named views, capture sequencing, and viewport coherence
- [6] Block definitions, instances, live/archive linked state, placement, replacement, graph/audit, events, cleanup, preview/export, and management

## Rules

- Capture full Rhino capability behind one operation rail per category; do not mirror native calls as public wrappers.
- Preserve document receipts, redraw/commit behavior, resource lifetimes, disposal, UI-thread protection, and native consistency at the category boundary.
- Keep document mutation, selection, construction, UI, camera, capture, block, and exchange ownership separated.
- Convert nullable, bool, obsolete, disposable, and synchronous native surfaces into typed `Fin`, `Option`, receipt, policy, and scoped-resource rails.
- Verify risky Rhino behavior against current RhinoWIP XML, decompile evidence when XML is absent, and `uv run python -m tools.quality api doctor|xml|types|decompile`.

## Known RhinoWIP Constraints

- `ViewTable.Reorder` or `MoveTo` is not public; sheet reorder rebinds `PageNumber`.
- `RhinoPageView` page size cannot be mutated post-creation through public setters.
- `File3dm.WriteWithLog`, `RhinoDoc.WriteFile`, and linked-resource refresh are synchronous.
- `File3dm.ReadWithLog` loads archives rather than streaming chunks.
- `FilePdf.SetCustomPages` replaces previously added pages, so mixed sheet and blank-page PDF publishing must sequence `AddPage`.
- `File3dm.Audit` and `IsValid` are deprecated and report success unconditionally.
- Detail layer overrides can be written per viewport, but RhinoCommon exposes no direct override enumeration API.

## Validation

Use `uv run python -m tools.quality static fix [paths...]` for cleanup. Add `uv run python -m tools.quality static build [paths...]`, managed specs, or `uv run python -m tools.quality bridge verify <scenario-or-glob>` when compile, managed behavior, or runtime document, viewport, block, file, capture, or construction behavior changes.
